Not in front of the cashier’s desk, to withdraw money or make deposits, but in front of the customer service desk, where old customers order checkbooks, tourists ask for directions to the Macy’s department store and new customers open accounts.
Many of those in front of me, I would then learn from Starr, my “trusted banker”, were in line for the same reason.
Unlike me, however, they have already taken their savings from the smaller banks from the places they commute from, such as New Jersey, Pennsylvania and Staten Island.
They have taken money from so-called thrifts (a bit like a construction company), credit unions, and types of city savings banks whose branches operate only within a state, and they say they treat customers like family.
