You meet or confront people, characters that sometimes you don’t even know or who give you only a few minutes to take the picture.
Beyond these circumstances, as a photographer, I always try to concretize my ideas.
The collection of portraits of contemporary flamenco, entitled "Flamenco-people" is set up at the El Fot<0xC3><0xB3>mata gallery, at number 20 in via de la Mata, parallel to via Alameda de Hercules, and will be open to the public until next October 16.
