The titles of his dances suggested me some basic elements of flamenco.
So, "la danza de la mariposa" suggested me a guajira, or "la danza de la serpiente" some tangos.
His dancing was sensual and I was told that my dancing was part of that aesthetic as well,” she explains.
The staging includes two exceptional contributions: that of Miguel Poveda, who will sing again Isabel in one of his shows, as face in "La puerta aberta"; and that of the teacher Matilde Coral, who exceptionally wanted to work with the one who had been a student of his.
"Matilde plays Tortola as an adult, the character of maturity.
