Industry prices continue to rise
The prices of domestic industrial sales in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - informs the Hungarian Central Institute of Statistics.
The prices of export sales of the industry reported in July 2008 were higher by 1.1%, compared to the previous year they decreased by 3.9%
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than the previous month and 3.2% higher than a year ago.
The prices of domestic industrial sales compared to the previous month increased by only 0.1%.
The prices of domestic sales of the processing sector also rose to a minimum, 0.1%, compared to July.
The largest increase in prices in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and shoe production with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastic and chemical raw materials caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in wood processing (0.1%).
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry there was an increase in prices of between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the field of electricity, gas, steam and water supply prices increased in August by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in the price of gas carried out by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared to 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the sectors of the processing industry, the largest increases were in the processing of petroleum products (32.4%).
In the manufacture of products derived from metal processing, the price increase was 13.2%, 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco representing a decisive weight.
There was a decrease in prices in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry, the rate of price increase varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the processing industry in the past year prices rose by 10.2%.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector were 18.7% higher than last year.
In domestic sales among the target groups of sectors, the largest monthly price increase occurred in August in sectors producing capital goods (0.7%).
In the sectors that produce consumer goods prices grew by 0.3%, in the energy and subsequent use sector prices did not change from those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the increase in larger prices was observed in the energy and subsequent use sector (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
The prices of industrial export sales calculated in florins grew in August by 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared to a decrease of 3.9% in 12 months.
The Hungarian forint weakened against the euro by 1.7% in the space of a month, against the dollar by 7.1%, compared to August 2007 it strengthened by 7.5% against the euro and by 15.9% against the dollar.
