The Italian version can be downloaded at http://en.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html and has been added to the English version that was on the mirrors since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, as usual the suite is also available for the Linux operating system.
On request, the installation CD can also be sent to your home or workplace.
And if the theme of gratuitousness can be a driving force for the diffusion in the homes, it is precisely in the business field that Open Office the suite tries the big bet, already being able to count on several projects realized in the public administration and in the schools.
And there is no shortage of companies that offer an ideal training, consulting and assistance service for small and medium-sized companies, which could open up business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for the videowriting equivalent of Word; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for the emulation presentations of Powerpoint; Dbase, as in the case of the most famous Access is the program that allows you to work on databases; Draw, is finally the graphic module.
The goal for 2008 is to reach 5 million downloads, and considering that today we are at almost 3 million and 600 thousand, with the release of the new version it is likely that we can also exceed the expected figure.
